HEADWORD: Separating
<hw>Sep"a*ra`ting</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <def>Designed or
employed to separate.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Separating funnel</b></col> <fld>(Chem.)</fld>, <cd>a
funnel, often globe-shaped, provided with a stopcock for the separate
drawing off of immiscible liquids of different specific
gravities.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Separation</ent>⟦br⟧
